properties.name: args
properties.summary: the original object argument to the IO call.

properties.name: canDelete
properties.summary: For dojo/io/script calls only, indicates whether the script tag that represents the request can be deleted after callbacks have been called. Used internally to know when cleanup can happen on JSONP-type requests.

properties.name: handleAs
properties.summary: The final indicator on how the response will be handled.

properties.name: id
properties.summary: For dojo/io/script calls only, the internal script ID used for the request.

properties.name: json
properties.summary: For dojo/io/script calls only: holds the JSON response for JSONP-type requests. Used internally to hold on to the JSON responses. You should not need to access it directly -- the same object should be passed to the success callbacks directly.

properties.name: query
properties.summary: For non-GET requests, the name1=value1&name2=value2 parameters sent up in the request.

properties.name: url
properties.summary: The final URL used for the call. Many times it will be different than the original args.url value.

properties.name: xhr
properties.summary: For XMLHttpRequest calls only, the XMLHttpRequest object that was used for the request.
